# Line-ending policy — critical for a cross-platform, GitHub-hosted plugin.
#
# The engine `bin/runcode` is an extensionless, shebang'd Python script that
# macOS/Linux run DIRECTLY (`#!/usr/bin/env python3`). If git ever checks it
# out with CRLF (a Windows clone with core.autocrlf=true would do exactly
# that), the shebang becomes `…/python3\r` and POSIX fails it with
# "bad interpreter: No such file or directory". So pin every text file to LF…
* text=auto eol=lf

# …force the engine + tests to LF no matter the client's autocrlf setting…
bin/runcode      text eol=lf
tests/test_engine.py text eol=lf

# …and keep the Windows shim as CRLF (cmd.exe is happiest with CRLF).
bin/runcode.cmd  text eol=crlf
